Preheat the oven to 170C/150C Fan/Gas 3.Rub the shoulder of lamb all over with the olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Arrange the rosemary, garlic and onion in the bottom of a deep-sided roasting tin and pour in 200ml/7fl oz water. Put the lamb on top and cover with kitchen foil.Roast the lamb for 3–4 hours, basting every hour or so with the juices in the roasting tray. After 2 hours, remove the kitchen foil and continue to cook until the meat is very tender and falling off the bone. Remove the lamb from the tray and set aside to rest.Put the Jersey Royals and sprigs of mint in a saucepan, cover with water and bring to the boil. Cook for 10–15 minutes, or until the potatoes are tender. Drain.For the mint sauce, put the mint, sugar and vinegar in a bowl and mix well.Shred the lamb on a serving plate and pour over the gravy. Serve with the Jersey Royals and the mint sauce.